# Agent Telemetry and Cost Rules

- Every provider interaction should emit an `ai_agent_events` record for start/completion/failure flows.
- Track per-agent usage in `agent_usage_events` with normalized units:
  - tokens
  - audio seconds
  - transcription seconds
  - tool call counts
  - estimated cost
- When cost data is available, also persist billable usage in `tenant_usage_costs` (via existing billing helpers) so tenant-level billing dashboards stay aligned.
- Include `trace_id` where possible to correlate events across router, provider, and billing logs.
- Never log raw secrets/API keys in telemetry payloads.
- Keep cross-tenant data out of analytics results unless user is explicitly in platform-admin context.
